<br>
My hand to hand is maxed, my 1hb is climbing fast at 65ish... I am keeping my 1hb in my primary for now until it is maxed also.  At that time, should I:<br>
<br>
options:<br>
<br>
1) Put the lower damage lower delay in primary (since the primary is the only weapon slot that gets my damage bonus)<br>
<br>
2) Put the higher damage higher delay 1hb in my primary since it has a higher DPS.<br>
<br>
Further questions:<br>
<br>
A.) Is it ALWAYS better to put your higher DPS in your primary?<br>
<br>
B.) How does double attack work?  ie.  Every time I swing with my primary I get a chance to swing with my secondary, or they do not relate as such.  If every time I swing with my primary, maybe I should put the faster weapon in my primary hand.  <br>
<br>
I have a log parser that I will be looking at once my 1hb is maxed, but was wondering if anyone had some insight that might help out.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Krosseyed Fumblefingerss<br>
23 Iksar Monk, Bristlebane<br>
<br>
