<br>
Since the primary hand automatically attacks each Delay cycle while the secondary hand does not, you should always put the &quot;better&quot; weapon in the primary hand. However, the definition of &quot;better&quot; changes as the Damage Bonus increases with your level.<br>
<br>
Double Attack gives you a chance of 2 attacks each cycle with your primary hand. The chance of success is believed to be (Level + skill)/500. Once your Double Attack skill reaches 150, you will also have a chance for a second hit with your secondary hand each time the Dual Wield check is successful. Even though the animations for the 2 hits run sequentially, to the game server they occur simultaneously.<br>
<br>
You also seem confused as to how Dual Wield works. Each hand has its own timer. Each time the Delay cycles on the weapon in your secondary hand, you get a Dual Wield skill check. If successful, you attack with that hand; if unsuccessful, you do not attack with the secondary hand that cycle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/18/02 7:09:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1611.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Correction</span><hr size=1> That should read :<br>
