<br>
1. It only applies to hits with the primary hand<br>
<br>
2. For all 1-handed weapons (including fists), the Damage Bonus = (Level-25)/3, rounded down<br>
<br>
3. For 2-handed weapons, the Damage Bonus varies with the Delay of the weapon as well as the Level of the wielder, so that slower weapons get larger bonuses.<br>
<br>
4. The Damage Bonus is ADDED to each hit (with the primary hand). With 1-handed weapons, this definitely means that more frequent hits yield more bonus damage in the same period of time.<br>
<br>
5. If you see someone auctioning a 1-handed weapon, and touting its great Damage Bonus as a selling point, ignore them : the Damage Bonus is entirely determined by the level of the wielder, so you may not get the same bonus at the time of purchase. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrosseyedfumblefingerss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>krosseyed fumblefingerss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/18/02 11:25:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1611.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage Bonus</span><hr size=1> That helps much.  Thank you. So to sum up... keep the higher DPS in my primary until my lower delay weapon's base damage + damage bonus &gt; greater delay weapon's base damage (which will be ... does the math... 31)<br>
